PN,30702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,FSpeaking from inside Tehran's
OL,7,Fnotorious Evin Prison in her first
OL,8,Finterview since the war began, Lindsay
OL,9,FForeman told ITV News about life under
OL,10,Fbombardment.
OL,12,FShe exists in a prison shaken by
OL,13,Fconflict, but where she runs laps of
OL,14,Fthe courtyard and bakes shortbread for
OL,15,Ffellow inmates, to provide small
OL,16,Fcomforts against the sound of
OL,17,Fexplosions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,F"When the bombs were going off at
OL,7,Fnight, in those first four nights, we
OL,8,Fwere all hiding under the bed", she
OL,9,Ftells me.
OL,11,F"So we were in metal-framed bunk beds,
OL,12,Fand we would get into the bottom bunk.
OL,13,FPeople were hyperventilating,
OL,14,Fscreaming.
OL,16,F"The first day you could feel it, the
OL,17,Fimpact of the bombs, the rockets, the
OL,18,Fmissiles," she said, referring to the
OL,19,Foutbreak of the conflict on February
OL,20,F28.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@^O]sD@AOUxD@AOUzD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,F"The building shook. I was actually on
OL,7,Fthe phone to Joe (Lindsay's son) when
OL,8,Fone of the bombs struck quite close
OL,9,Fby. We were estimating maybe a couple
OL,10,Fof kilometres away and the building
OL,11,Fshook."
OL,13,FDuring a thirty-minute interview with
OL,14,FITV News, conducted over a crackly
OL,15,Fprison phone line, she described
OL,16,Fhearing the "whistling noise of
OL,17,Fmissiles and the hum of the drones".
OL,26,@oD@RpmoD@`pnsD@GO]xD@MOUyD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,FShe said some inmates ` terrified, but
OL,7,Fhopeful ` cheered as the bombs fell,
OL,8,Fbelieving they might signal the
OL,9,Fcollapse of the regime holding them.
OL,11,F"We would hear the bombs, and then we
OL,12,Fwould ask what they were. So they were
OL,13,Fcalling them bunker busters, where the
OL,14,Fnoise is like 'duh-duh-duh-duh-dum-
OL,15,Fdum.'
OL,17,F"And then the ground shakes. You can
OL,18,Ffeel the depth and you just think, my
OL,19,FGod, that must have done some serious
OL,20,Fdamage."
OL,26,@sD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,FShe gave a haunting description of the
OL,7,Faftermath of a strike on an oil
OL,8,Ffacility close to the prison shortly
OL,9,Fafter the start of the war.
OL,11,F"I think it was on day three or four.
OL,12,FThey must have hit some kind of
OL,13,Fpetroleum site or something. And the
OL,14,Fsky was black. So at 8, 9, 10 o'clock
OL,15,Fin the morning, it was like nighttime
OL,16,Fbecause the sky was so dark."
OL,26,@sD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,FInside the prison, she says staffing
OL,7,Flevels have dropped since the war
OL,8,Fbegan, with some of those still on
OL,9,Fduty no longer carrying arms. But
OL,10,Fgiven the uncertainty, she has been
OL,11,Fforced to confront the possibility she
OL,12,Fmay not survive.
OL,14,F"When the buildings shake, there is
OL,15,Fnowhere to go. These buildings are not
OL,16,Fdesigned for safety. There's no fire
OL,17,Fescape, there's no access to the
OL,18,Foutside for us. If the building
OL,19,Fcollapses, that will be the end."
OL,26,@vD@AOU{D@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,F"And sometimes just living it, just
OL,7,Faccepting it, just knowing that there
OL,8,Fis a chance of dying and making peace
OL,9,Fwith that."
OL,11,FLindsay and her husband, Craig, were
OL,12,Farrested while travelling through Iran
OL,13,Fin January 2025 and were later accused
OL,14,Fof espionage, charges they deny.
OL,16,FBoth are now held alongside political
OL,17,Fprisoners at Evin.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,FShe says a call this week with the
OL,7,FBritish ambassador offered some hope,
OL,8,Fthough her family believe the UK
OL,9,Fgovernment has not done enough to help.
OL,11,FBut she fears that as senior figures
OL,12,Fin Iran's regime are eliminated, the
OL,13,Fwindow to negotiate her release is
OL,14,Fclosing.
OL,16,F"I empathise wholly with what they (UK
OL,17,Fdiplomats) are trying to do, given the
OL,18,Fpeople that they're trying to do it
OL,19,Fwith, a lot of them have been killed."
OL,26,@xD@AOUxD@dpmyD@Jpn{D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,F"We know from the media here that a
OL,7,Flot of the senior officials in all
OL,8,Fareas of government, security... have
OL,9,Fbeen assassinated. So I know they
OL,10,Fcan't talk to a lot of these people
OL,11,Fbecause they are no longer here."
OL,13,F"Sometimes we just have to take
OL,14,Fresponsibility for the situation we
OL,15,Ffind ourselves in, that we create. I
OL,16,Fchose to come here. I'm not going to
OL,17,Fblame the (UK) government for that."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@aO]uD@AOUyD@KpmyD@NpnyD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,FAlthough their cells are just metres
OL,7,Faway, Craig and Lindsay Foreman are
OL,8,Frarely allowed to meet. But a last-
OL,9,Fminute meeting was authorised on
OL,10,FTuesday, allowing the couple to talk
OL,11,Fand drink tea together for the first
OL,12,Ftime in two months.
OL,14,F"Well, there were very extreme
OL,15,Femotions because initially I was like,
OL,16,Famazing. And then it's like, what's
OL,17,Fgoing on? One hour we get, once or
OL,18,Ftwice a month. You haven't seen each
OL,19,Fother for two months, so we've got one
OL,20,Fhour and it's the best hour that you
OL,21,Fcan have."
OL,26,@vD@AOU}D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
