PN,30714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,FTheir ten-year terms are considered
OL,7,Funusually long - twice the five-year
OL,8,Fsentence imposed on Nazanin Zaghari-
OL,9,FRatcliffe, the British-Iranian dual
OL,10,Fnational whose detention became one of
OL,11,Fthe most high-profile diplomatic
OL,12,Fdisputes between London and Tehran.
OL,14,FLindsay Foreman is clear about the
OL,15,Frisks faced by the prisoners.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774515911
OL,3,CBritish woman jailed in Iran gives
OL,4,Cfirst interview since the war began
OL,6,F"I don't know how it will end, and I
OL,7,Fdon't know how it will end well. And
OL,8,Fthat's what's hard day-to-day at the
OL,9,Fmoment, is how and when will it end?
OL,10,FAnd what does "good" look like when we
OL,11,Fcome out of the other side?"
OL,13,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,14,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,15,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,16,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,17,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,18,Fbelow...
